Steps to get the SSM certification

Not sure where to get started with your SAFe 5 Scrum Master certification? Just follow these simple steps and validate your expertise as a Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master.

..... View more

1. Get trained

Get trained by a Scaled Agile authorized training partner and attend the 16-hour training delivered by a SAFe Program Consultant (SPC) who’s also an expert practitioner.

2. Take the SAFe Scrum Master exam 

On successful completion of the two-day training, you will receive information on the exam along with your login credentials, directly from Scaled Agile. Log in using your credentials and take the 90-minute, 45-MCQ online closed-book exam. Clear the exam and get 34 out of 45 questions right to pass the SAFe 5 Scrum Master exam and 33 out of 45 questions right to pass the SAFe 4 Scrum Master exam. 

3. You're now a Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master!

On passing the exam, you become a Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master. You will receive your SAFe 5 Scrum Master PDF Certificate and Digital Badge within 5-7 working days.

SAFe 5 Scrum Master Course

  • Facilitate Scrum events across teams 
  • Facilitate effective Iteration execution 
  • Support effective Program Increment execution 
  • Support relentless improvement 
  • Coach Agile teams to gain maximum business results

Our Certified SAFe Scrum Master training aims to equip you with all the skills to be an effective SAFe Scrum Master. In this engaging and interactive two-day program, you will develop the practical skills employers look for in a SAFe Scrum Master:

  • Leadership
  • Coaching
  • Change management

  • Conflict management
  • Facilitation
  • Lean-Agile management

  • Delivering the maximum business value at scale

PDUs and SEUs

1. How many PDUs and SEUs will I be eligible for?

You will earn 16 PDUs and 16 SEUs by participating in our two-day training program.

2. How many PDUs will I need to maintain my SAfe Scrum Master (SSM) certification?

You will need 10 continuing education or outreach hours (PDUs) to maintain your SAFe SSM certification. 

3. What are PDUs and SEUs?

PDUs are Professional Development Units issued by the Project Management Institute®. They can be earned by completing educational training or learning opportunities, which serve to validate your participation and continued proficiency in the principles and practices of project management. 

PDUs are the measuring unit used to quantify your project management professional development as part of the PMI’s Continuing Certification Requirements (CCR) program. 1 PDU = 1 hour of learning/activity. 

A Scrum Education Unit® (SEU®) is a credit issued by Scrum Alliance®, validating your participation and continued proficiency in the fundamental principles of Scrum. SEUs demonstrate that you are furthering your proficiency as a Scrum practitioner. SEUs follow a 1:1 ratio, where one hour of participation or preparation towards increasing your proficiency in Scrum is equal to one SEU. 

4. What are some of the ways to earn PDUs?

You can earn PDUs by attending training programs offered by PMI Accredited Training Organizations (ATOs) or by organizations or universities. Whenever you attend a PMI congress, webinar, conference or any other event or indulge in self-directed learning, you can earn PDUs. 

5. Where can I find out more about PDUs?

You can find out more about PDUs in PMI’s FAQs. 

6. Where can I find out more about SEUs?

Our blog will help you learn more about how to earn an SEU from Scrum Alliance. Get all the information you need to take advantage of SEUs for your professional growth, namely: 

  • What are SEUs and why you need them 
  • How to earn SEUs 
  • Types of continuing education opportunities that qualify for SEUs  
  • How to calculate the value of an SEU for Scrum Alliance certifications 
  • How to log SEUs for Scrum Alliance certifications 
  • How recent SEUs need to be 
  • How to determine whether a previously accumulated SEU can be used for Scrum Alliance certifications 
  • List of SEU resources put together by Scrum Alliance  
  • Where you can utilize SEUs you have accumulated  

For further information about SEUs and PDUs, please reach us at support@knowledgehut.com.  

Certification Process

1. Who provides the SAFe Scrum Master (SSM) certification?

Scaled Agile, Inc.® is the provider of the Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe), the most popular method for scaling agile at the enterprise level. SAFe was initially released in 2011 by Dean Leffingwell as a knowledgebase for enterprises to adopt Agile. The Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master certification is given to those who have successfully undertaken the SAFe Scrum Master Certification Exam. 

2. Can I get certified without taking the SAFe® 5 Scrum Master course?

You cannot get certified without taking the course. Scaled Agile believes in true learning that can only be achieved through in-person training and hands-on experience from a SAFe Program Consultant (SPC). The SAFe Scrum Master exam is not provided as a substitute for formal training. 

3. What do I get with the SAFe® 5 Scrum Master course?

When you enrol for the SAFe Scrum Master certification course, you will receive the following: 

  • Certified SAFe Scrum Master Certificate (PDF format) 
  • Certified SAFe Scrum Master Digital Badge 
  • One-year membership to the SAFe Community Platform
  • Access to SAFe events and MeetUp Groups  
  • Various SAFe learning resources
4. What is the process to become a SAFe Scrum Master?

Here’s the process to become a Certified SAFe Scrum Master: 

  1. Get trained by an authorized training partner of Scaled Agile. Attend the two-day training delivered by a SAFe Program Consultant (SPC) who’s also an expert practitioner. 
  2. On successful completion of the two-day training, you will receive information on the exam along with your login credentials, directly from Scaled Agile.  
  3. Log in using your credentials and take the 90-minute,, 45-MCQ online closed-book exam. 
  4. Get 34 out of 45 questions right to pass the SAFe 5 exam and 33 out of 45 questions right to pass the SAFe 4 exam. 
  5. On passing the exam, you become a Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master. You will receive your SAFe 5 Scrum Master PDF Certificate and Digital Badge within 5-7 working days. 

Ready to get started with your Certified SAFe Scrum Master certification? Click here.

5. Do you provide a course completion certificate?

Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate on completing the course.  

6. How long does it take to get a Certified SAFe 5 Scrum Master certification?

You will have to attend two days of training under a SAFe Program Consultant (SPC) following which you will be required to take an exam to demonstrate your knowledge of SAFe and to get certified. Once you pass the exam, you are declared certified.  

7. Will my certificate say ‘Virtual’ if I take the certification online?

No, your certificate will not mention the mode of course you have attended. It will look the same as the in-person certificates.  

8. Why should I renew my SAFe Scrum Master certification?

The Scaled Agile framework is evolving, all thanks to the engagements and contributions of those who share their ideas as well as practical experiences in the workplace. Renewal of your certification validates your interest in keeping up with the latest best practices in SAFe® and your commitment to professional excellence.

9. What is the process to renew my certification?
Your certification needs to be renewed every year. The following must be fulfilled each year, prior to renewal:
  • PDUs: A minimum of 10 continuing education/outreach hours (PDUs) need to be added each year.
  • Certification Renewal Cost: You will need to purchase the bundled product which includes Membership and Certification and comes at a price of $295 ($100 for renewal and $195 for membership). If you possess more than one certification from Scaled Agile, you can renew all of them together at this cost. For example, if you have a Leading SAFe certification expiring on 6 April 2021 and an SASM certification expiring on 10 October 2021, when you pay $295, both certifications will get renewed and will have the same expiry of 10 October 2021 or whichever is the later date. 
Here are the steps to renew your certification:
  • Log in to the SAFe Community platform using your credentials.
  • Click on the "Renew" button next to your certification (located at the top of the homepage)
  • You will then be presented with the payment Screen (Shopping Cart), allowing you to complete the renewal process. 

10. What if I do not want to renew my certification, but remain a member of the SAFe Community Platform?

In that case, you will only need to pay $195 and continue to benefit from all the valuable content and interactions at the SAFe Community Platform.

11. Which is the latest version of SAFe?

The latest release of the Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe) is version 5, update 5.1. KnowledgeHut's Leading SAFe 5 Certification course is aligned with the latest version of SAFe.

12. Is SAFe 5 now version SAFe 5.1?

No. The version of SAFe remains SAFe 5. The change from SAFe 5 to 5.1 is simply a set of updates to SAFe 5. One of these updates includes a new SAFe 5.1 Big Picture, but this and the other updates, are all in support of SAFe 5 for Lean Enterprises.

13. What is the difference between an upgrade and an update pertaining to the latest SAFe version?

An upgrade is when a significantly changed version of the Scaled Agile Framework® (SAFe®) is released; this is recognized typically by an increase in the major version number (e.g. 4 to 5).

Updates are when incremental changes are made to the existing version of the Framework and no upgrade is required.  Updates do not require a retest if you already have the most up-to-date certification available, and no upgrade is required.

The change from SAFe 5 to 5.1 is an update, not an upgrade. 

14. Why is Scaled Agile Inc. releasing these updates to SAFe 5?

With a commitment to supporting and evolving SAFe practices, Scaled Agile is on a mission to meet the ever-changing needs of SAFe Enterprises and Partner communities. Towards this end, Scaled Agile will continually update their existing articles and keep adding new ones to reflect the updated understanding from the SAFe community and practitioners on best practices in Lean Agile at scale.

15. What new framework guidance is included in the latest SAFe 5.1 update?

The latest update 5.1 was rolled out to the latest version, SAFe 5 on February 10, 2021. The key updates are as follows:

  • An updated Big Picture (now at version 5.1) 
  • New guidance for operational and development value streams to support organizing around value, the #1 request from our customers 
  • ART and Team Topologies, patterns for organizing teams and ARTs to improve flow. 
  • New guidance around DevSecOps technical skills and tools that power the Continuous Delivery Pipeline. 
  • Integrated Participatory Budgeting, a dynamic and collaborative process of allocating funding to value streams. 
  • Specific guidance for applying Lean-Agile practices to business and technology domains, including a new SAFe for Hardware article.

More information can be found on Scaled Agile.

Digital Badge

1. What is a Digital Badge?

A digital badge is an online image of your SAFe Certification that enables you to verify, share, post, and manage your SAFe expertise in real-time, via any platform. The Digital Badge, issued by Acclaim, the exclusive certifying entity for Scaled Agile. Your digital badge authenticates your certification and demonstrates your expertise in SAFe and commitment to professional excellence.  

2. How do I get a Digital Badge? Is it necessary?

To receive the Digital Badge go to the Privacy Preference Settings within the SAFe Community Platform and opt for it. Availing a Digital Badge is completely your decision; it is not mandatory. 

3. How will I know if I have received a Digital Badge?

You will receive an e-mail from no-reply@youracclaim.com with the instructions to claim your badge. The mail will also have information on setting-up your account for certification management and sharing. To know more, please visit http://support.youracclaim.com.  

4. What are the benefits of a Digital Badge?

A Digital Badge comes with the following benefits: 

  • You can share your expertise in a simple, secure, and easily verifiable format. 
  • Employers have a better insight about your experience-level and capabilities. 
  • You can search as well as apply for job opportunities via the Acclaim platform. 
5. Where and how can I share my badge via Acclaim?

You can share your Digital Badge directly from the Acclaim Platform: 

  • On social media platforms including Twitter, Facebook, and LinkedIn 
  • On email 
  • In your email signature
  • You can also embed it on your website
6. Do I have to pay an additional fee for Digital Badge? How long will the badge be valid?

No. Digital Badge is included as part of your SAFe Community subscription benefits. The Badge will remain valid as long as you are a member of SAFe Community Platform. In case your membership expires, or you don’t renew it, the badge page will display the message “Expired”.  

7. Can someone else copy my badge?

Though badges are simply digital image files, they are linked to unique verified data, making them more secure and reliable than any other form of certificate. Therefore, it eliminates the possibility of anyone copying your certification as well as your associated identity. 

8. In case I face any issues with my badge, who do I contact?

Visit http://support.youracclaim.com/ for issues related to:  

  • Acclaim platform/account  
  • Badge sharing/display 

Write to support@scaledagile.com if you haven’t received any badge notifications even after earning a SAFe4 or later certification or if you want to retrieve a badge that you rejected or deleted in Acclaim.  

SAFe Scrum Master Exam

1. What is the SAFe Scrum Master exam pattern and passing score?
  • The SAFe Scrum Master certification exam is a closed-book test taken online.  
  • The test comes with 45 multiple-choice questions which you are required to answer within 90-minutes (exam duration).  
  • You need to get 33 out of 45 questions right to pass the SSM 4 exam and 34 out of 45 questions right to pass the SSM 5 exam. 
2. What is the difficulty level of the SAFe Scrum Master (SSM) exam?

The SAFe SSM exam is a closed-book exam and is not difficult to pass, provided you have received the required training. Our intensive coaching and exam preparation activities are all geared towards helping you pass the exam on the first attempt.  

3. Where can I find the link to take the exam?

Once you complete your 16-hour course, you will receive a welcome email from Scaled Agile, Inc. This email will contain the link that will redirect you to the exam page. 

4. Will I be able to pause the test and return to it later?

No, you will have a time limit of 90 minutes and will not be able to pause the test. In case you accidentally close the window, you will be able to reopen it immediately. If you lose the internet connection or access to the test for an extended period, you will have to reach out to support@scaledagile.com.

5. If I fail, can I apply for a re-evaluation?

There is no re-evaluation for the exam. However, if you fail you can retake the exam.  

6. Can I retake the SAFe Scrum Master certification test if I fail? How soon?

Yes, the first exam attempt is included as a part of the course registration fee if, the exam is taken within 30 days of course completion.  

  • Each subsequent retake attempt costs $50.  
  • The second exam attempt (first retake) can be done immediately after the first attempt.  
  • The third attempt has a 10-day waiting period and the fourth attempt has a 30-day waiting period. 

For more details read Scaled Agile’s Exam Retake Policy. 

7. Can I retake the exam if I score poorly? How soon?

No, you are not allowed to retake the exam if you have already passed the test and scored poorly. Your test score is only available to you. Nobody else will be able to see your score of the test.  

8. How long does it take to receive SAFe Scrum Master exam results?

You will get your results immediately after you attempt the exam and click on the submit button.  

9. How many attempts do I have to pass the SAFe Scrum Master exam?

There are no limits to the number of times you can attempt the exam, if you ready to pay for it. The Scaled Agile, Inc. allows you to take the first attempt at no cost, within 30 days of the course completion. Thereafter, each retake attempt costs $50.

SAFe® 5 Scrum Master Training and Certification FAQs

SAFe Scrum Master Certifications

1. What is the SAFe Scrum Master all about?
The SAFe 5 Scrum Master (SSM) certification is a designation offered by Scaled Agile, Inc. (Scaled Agile) to practitioners who complete a two-day training by a SAFe Program Consultant and showcase their understanding of SAFe by passing the SAFe 5 Scrum Master certification exam.
2. Which is better, SAFe Scrum Master or CSM?

The SAFe Scrum Master is a credential that certifies individuals on the use of the Scaled Agile framework. It is offered by the Scaled Agile to professionals who have a minimum of five years of experience and demonstrate an understanding of Lean thinking and implementing the ART by passing the exam.

The Certified ScrumMaster (CSM) on the other hand is an entry-level credential offered by Scrum Alliance and is a good starting point for those who wish to start their career in Scrum and learn about Agile principles, roles, Scrum framework, values, artifacts, planning, organising, and executing.

Both credentials have a good standing in the industry and help professionals get good opportunities. What you choose to pursue depends on your previous experience and your future requirements. If you are SAFe experienced, then it is recommended that you go for the SSM credential. 

3. What is the difference between SAFe Scrum Master and SAFe Agilist?

Both the SAFe Scrum Master and SAFe Agilist are credentials offered by the Scaled Agile, Inc.

SAFe Agilist helps professionals get a thorough introduction to the SAFe framework and help usher the lean-agile mindset in the enterprise context. It’s a great credential for leadership and managerial roles involved in leading change and instilling a DevOps culture.

The SAFe Scrum Master helps professionals validate their Scrum expertise at the enterprise level. SAFe Scrum masters lead their teams in tandem with the entire organization and deliver value at scale. 

SSM Certification

1. Is the SAFe Scrum Master certification worth it?

The SAFe Scrum Master certification is certainly worth the effort. Armed with this certification, you can validate your knowledge and expertise and your commitment to continued excellence and quality. The certification helps you:

  • Showcase your proficiency in SAFe and applying Scrum at the enterprise-level  
  • It helps you get noticed and accelerate your career growth  
  • It helps you get noticed at interviews or for promotions at your current job 
  • Earn higher salaries than non-certified professionals
2. What are the career benefits you gain with SSM Certification?

The SSM certification gives you a number of career benefits

  • Earn salaries as high as $123k annually (PayScale) 
  • Be part of the 800,00+ strong SAFe practitioner community 
  • Get jobs across industries including telecom, oil and gas, finance, government, healthcare and more 
  • Earn more than your non-certified peers 
  • Open yourself to a sea of opportunities (70% of Fortune 100 companies employ SAFe)

SSM Certification Validity

1. What is the validity of SAFe Scrum Master Certification?

The SAFe Scrum Master Certification is valid only for 1 year and needs to be renewed each year.

SSM Certification Cost

1. How much does the SAFe Scrum Master Certification cost?

The certification cost is included in the training cost.

Training Cost in India: Rs 55999, Cost in the U.S.: USD 1099.

First exam attempt is included as part of the course registration fee if the exam is taken within 30 days of course completion. Each retake attempt costs $50.

Candidates must have at least one year of experience working in a Lean-Agile environment.

SSM Certification Exam

1. What is the difficulty level of the SAFe Scrum Master (SSM) exam? Or Is SAFe Scrum Master Exam difficult?

The SAFe SSM exam is a closed-book exam and is not difficult to pass, provided you have received the required training. Our intensive coaching and exam preparation activities are all geared towards helping you pass the exam on the first attempt.

2. Is SAFe Scrum Master Exam open book?

No. It is a closed book exam.

SSM Exam Prep

1. How to prepare for SAFe Scrum Master Certification Exam?

The first step towards preparing for the SAFe Scrum Master Certification Exam is to attend the SAFe Scrum Master course. This will help you gain an in-depth understanding of all the concepts and also give you access to all the resources and study materials.

2. How do I pass the SAFe scrum master exam?

The SAFe Scrum Master exam is designed to measure knowledge and skill related to the job role. The exam is closed book and Scaled Agile recommends that candidates attend the training and do a thorough read of all the recommended resources before appearing for the exam.

PDUs and SEUs

1. How do I claim PDUs for my SAFe Scrum Master course?

On completion of the course you earn 16 PDUs and 16 SEUs. You can claim PDUs under PMI's ‘Education courses provided by other third-party providers’ category. You can claim your PDUs online at https://ccrs.pmi.org.
